sponseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Days 7-8 post-fertilisation","Days 11-12 post-fertilisation","Days 15-16 post-fertilisation","Days 18-19 post-fertilisation","Days 21-22 post-fertilisation"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eprechordal plate forms during days 15-16 post-fertilisation\u003C/strong\u003E in human embryonic development. This structure develops from migrating mesoderm cells during gastrulation and is essential for proper head development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent other key developmental timepoints:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDays 7-8\u003C/strong\u003E corresponds to early blastocyst implantation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDays 11-12\u003C/strong\u003E marks the formation of the bilaminar disc\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDays 18-19\u003C/strong\u003E represents the time of primitive streak elongation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDays 21-22\u003C/strong\u003E corresponds to neural tube formation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe prechordal plate serves as an important organising center that influences the development of forebrain structures and helps establish the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The prechordal plate forms during days 15-16 of human embryonic development, serving as an important organizer for head development.","The prechordal plate develops from migrating mesoderm cells during gastrulation."],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PM